-Let x double number , 0<= x <=1 taking x^(inf) = 0, just like taking probability for inf number of turns will also equal to zero.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Binomial distribution :
if you have 2 possible out comes A and B and need the probability of getting N Bs , X turns,
let probeility of getting B P2 and getting A p1,
P(X)= (P1^(X-N) * p2^(N) ) * (X-1 choose N-1)
E(X)= N/p2 .
